rawContent:
Rainbow queen 

Short story about #depression 

🫶🏾

Once upon a time, in a world overwhelmed by shadows and sadness, there was a queen named Iris. She was known as the Rainbow Queen, for she possessed a remarkable power: the ability to wield colors as her superpower. 

Deep within her heart, Queen Iris harbored a relentless battle against depression. The weight of darkness threatened to consume her spirit, but she refused to surrender. Instead, she turned to the vibrant hues of her kingdom for solace and strength. 

With a flick of her wrist and a determined gaze, Queen Iris conjured brilliant rainbows that spanned across the sky, casting a kaleidoscope of colors over her land. These radiant arcs of light spread joy, hope, and rejuvenation, lifting the hearts of her subjects. 

People flocked to witness the Rainbow Queen's incredible power, seeking respite from their own internal struggles. Her colorful magic washed away the shadows that plagued their minds, replacing them with a renewed sense of optimism. 

Yet, Queen Iris knew that battling depression required more than just her powers. She used her position to raise awareness about mental health, openly discussing her own struggles and encouraging her subjects to seek help when needed. 

The Rainbow Queen's compassion and strength inspired many, and soon her kingdom became a sanctuary for those suffering from depression. She established support networks, providing resources and counseling to those in need. Her colorful magic was not just a spectacle; it became a symbol of hope and healing. 

Over time, the Rainbow Queen's efforts began to transform her realm. The once somber land blossomed into a vibrant haven, filled with laughter, love, and acceptance. The shadows of depression no longer held the same power they once did, for the Rainbow Queen had shown her people that they were not alone in their struggles. 

Queen Iris's journey was not without its challenges. She faced moments when her own spirit faltered, when the darkness threatened to overcome her. Yet, she persevered, reminding herself of the strength she possessed within. She knew that her battle against depression was ongoing, but she also knew that she was not defined by it. 

And so, the Rainbow Queen continued to illuminate her kingdom with her colorful superpower, spreading light and hope wherever she went. Through her bravery and resilience, she proved that even in the face of the darkest shadows, the power of love, community, and embracing one's own uniqueness could conquer depression and bring forth a brighter, more vibrant world.

Once upon a time, in a world overwhelmed by shadows and sadness, there was a queen named Iris. She was known as the Rainbow Queen, for she possessed a remarkable power: the ability to wield colors as her superpower. 

Deep within her heart, Queen Iris harbored a relentless battle against depression. The weight of darkness threatened to consume her spirit, but she refused to surrender. Instead, she turned to the vibrant hues of her kingdom for solace and strength. 

With a flick of her wrist and a determined gaze, Queen Iris conjured brilliant rainbows that spanned across the sky, casting a kaleidoscope of colors over her land. These radiant arcs of light spread joy, hope, and rejuvenation, lifting the hearts of her subjects. 

People flocked to witness the Rainbow Queen's incredible power, seeking respite from their own internal struggles. Her colorful magic washed away the shadows that plagued their minds, replacing them with a renewed sense of optimism. 

Yet, Queen Iris knew that battling depression required more than just her powers. She used her position to raise awareness about mental health, openly discussing her own struggles and encouraging her subjects to seek help when needed. 

The Rainbow Queen's compassion and strength inspired many, and soon her kingdom became a sanctuary for those suffering from depression. She established support networks, providing resources and counseling to those in need. Her colorful magic was not just a spectacle; it became a symbol of hope and healing. 

Over time, the Rainbow Queen's efforts began to transform her realm. The once somber land blossomed into a vibrant haven, filled with laughter, love, and acceptance. The shadows of depression no longer held the same power they once did, for the Rainbow Queen had shown her people that they were not alone in their struggles. 

Queen Iris's journey was not without its challenges. She faced moments when her own spirit faltered, when the darkness threatened to overcome her. Yet, she persevered, reminding herself of the strength she possessed within. She knew that her battle against depression was ongoing, but she also knew that she was not defined by it. 

And so, the Rainbow Queen continued to illuminate her kingdom with her colorful superpower, spreading light and hope wherever she went. Through her bravery and resilience, she proved that even in the face of the darkest shadows, the power of love, community, and embracing one's own uniqueness could conquer depression and bring forth a brighter, more vibrant world.

media.altText:
Angst, Schuld, Scham presst Dich hinein in Deine Körperzellen, 
macht Deine Gefühlswelt und Dein Energiefeld zu. 
Diese erlebten Erfahrungen bleiben unverdaut und rauben Dir Deinen Atem. 

Bevor Du hier inkarnierst, definierst Du Lebensthemen als Seele und die erlebst Du hier bist zum Erbrechen. Bis in die tiefsten Qualen, bist diese Themen erkannt und durch Dein Bewusstsein im Resonanzfeld des Lebens losgelassen werden. So einfach ist das Lebens. Das Spiel Deines Lebens erkennen! Deine LebensRolle hier! 
Und die ist veränderbar. Ab dem Tag des Bewusstmachens. 

Ich gehe mit Dir in die Tiefe Deines SEINS!
Bis zu Deinem größten Schmerzpunkt.
Du kannst nichts vor mir verbergen…!
Ich höre und lese Deine Seele
über die Energie Deiner Worte!

Ich führe Menschen durch die Angst in Ihre Kraft! 

Sende mir eine Nachricht unter info@edwingasper.com oder ruf mich einfach an und nutze das kostenlose Erstgespräch: 0174-3263506

Preis: 200,- €
